'''Donna Atwood''' (February 14, 1923 â December 20, 2010) was an [[United States|American]] [[Figure skating|figure skater]].  She competed in [[pair skating]] and won the gold medal at the 1941 [[United States Figure Skating Championships]] with partner [[Eugene Turner]].<ref>[http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=vVUyAAAAIBAJ&sjid=UrYFAAAAIBAJ&pg=3933,3335359&dq=eugene-turner+donna-atwood&hl=en AP Story in Palm Beach Post, 3 Feb 1941]</ref>  In 1949, she married John H. Harris, the first owner of the Ice Capades, with whom she had two children.<ref>"Obituaries: John H. Harris, Showman, Dies; First Owner of Ice Capades", [[New York Times]], 13 Feb 1969 [http://news.google.com/archivesearch?q=donna.atwood+icecapades&btnG=Search&um=1&ned=us&hl=en&scoring=a]</ref>  She skated professionally with the [[Ice Capades]] for 16 years, retiring from the role of lead skater in 1956.<ref>"Ice Capades' Donna Atwood to Retire Soon", [[Los Angeles Times]], 8 Apr 1956 [http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/429352701.html?dids=429352701:429352701&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:AI&type=historic&date=Apr+08,+1956&author=&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=Ice+Capades'+Donna]</ref><ref>"Skaters' Waltz: 'Hollywood' Cast Joins Other Icers", Billboard, 22 Sep 1956 [http://books.google.com/books?id=iAoEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA84&dq=donna.atwood+ice.capades&hl=en&ei=Er7mS_bZNJGgkQWIuJnLBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=book-preview-link&resnum=3&ved=0CDkQuwUwAg#v=onepage&q=donna.atwood%20ice.capades&f=false]</ref>

Atwood died, aged 85, at the [[Motion Picture & Television Country House and Hospital]] on December 20, 2010.<ref>Nelson, Valerie J.: [http://www.kansascity.com/2011/01/20/2598776/donna-atwood-longtime-ice-capades.html Donna Atwood, longtime Ice Capades star, dies at 85], ''The Kansas City Star'', January 20, 2011.</ref>

